cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD 

The paper discusses the Bibliometric-enhanced Information Retrieval (BIR) workshops, which focus on information retrieval and bibliometrics in the context of scientific documents. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also mentions the use of scientific corpora and related information networks, which suggests the categories cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as likely options. Additionally, the paper discusses the creation, communication, and use of scientific knowledge, which could fall under the categories cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SD (Software Development and Programming Languages).
